<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Encompass" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Encompass,</orth> 1) to enclose, surround: <cit><quote>--ed with a winding maze,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1151" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1151</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>round --ed and set upon,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.114" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 114</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed with thy lustful paramours,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 53</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 15</bibl>. <cit><quote>--ed with your crown,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 3</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.204" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 204</bibl>. <cit><quote>her wide walks --ed but one man,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 155</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to obtain, get possession of, come by: <cit><quote>have I --ed you?</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 159</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Compass</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>